cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about neural network architectures and their co-optimization with neuromorphic hardware. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the design of neuromorphic hardware. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is a possible category as neuromorphic computing is an emerging technology. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper is about neural networks, which are a key component of AI. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the complete system level application of the hardware-software co-optimization.
